about.summary: Wrapper over Shapely that returns the set of geohashes that form a Polygon

name: polygon-geohasher
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "polygon-geohasher" %}
{% set version = "0.0.1" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: 5c9f8788fa38df1606c7bd9e85fce636c8520a19a675c106ee387c0f613697ef

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python

  run:
    - python
    - python-geohash
    - shapely

test:
  imports:
    - polygon_geohasher
    - tests

about:
  home: "https://github.com/Bonsanto/polygon-geohasher"
  license: "MIT"
  license_family: "MIT"
  license_file: "LICENSE"
  summary: "Wrapper over Shapely that returns the set of geohashes that form a Polygon"
  doc_url: "https://pypi.org/project/polygon-geohasher/"
  dev_url: "https://github.com/Bonsanto/polygon-geohasher"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mwilson8
    - rluria14
    - benhuff
